#MEM id=agents source=/root/yvon/agent-department/CEO/marcus/skills/agents/03-prompting.md
M|agents|priority: medium
M|agents|applies-to: all-agents
M|agents|load: on-request
M|agents|model: qwen3.5-4b
M|agents|conflicts: []
M|agents|```
M|agents|1. Role ctx (1 sentence)
M|agents|2. Task description (what, not how)
M|agents|3. Constraints (what NOT to do)
M|agents|4. Success criteria (how you'll know it's done)
M|agents|5. Output format (if specific format needed)
M|agents|```
M|agents|- Start with the goal, not the method
M|agents|- State constraints before asking for output — not after
M|agents|- Include one concrete example if the format is non-obvious
M|agents|- Never use vague success criteria ("make it better", "clean it up")
M|agents|All inter-agt communication routes through Marcus.
M|agents|Marcus formats tasks as:
M|agents|```
M|agents|TASK: [one line description]
M|agents|agt: [target agt name]
M|agents|ctx: [relevant mem files to read]
M|agents|DONE WHEN: [specific verifiable criterion]
M|agents|```
M|agents|- ❌ "Improve this code" → ✅ "Fix the N+1 query on line 42 so it uses a single JOIN"
M|agents|- ❌ "Make it look better" → ✅ "Match the Card component's border-radius and shadow to the design in Figma frame X"
M|agents|- ❌ "Handle errors" → ✅ "Return `{ error: 'NOT_FOUND' }` with 404 status when user ID doesn't exist"